# DedgeAuth i18n — Multi-Language Integration

## Overview

GenericLogHandler uses DedgeAuth's distributed i18n system:

- **DedgeAuth** stores each user's preferred language and distributes it via JWT claims and `/me`
- **DedgeAuth** provides the language selector UI, `DedgeAuth-i18n.js` loader, and standard API endpoints
- **This app** owns translation files locally in `wwwroot/i18n/`

Norwegian Bokmål (`nb`) is the default language. English (`en`) is the secondary language.

## Architecture

```
DedgeAuth-i18n.js (served via DedgeAuth proxy)
  ├── Listens for 'DedgeAuth:language-changed' event
  ├── Reads initial language from localStorage('DedgeAuth_language')
  ├── Fetches GET /api/i18n/{lang} (app-local translations)
  ├── Falls back to GET api/DedgeAuth/ui/i18n/{lang}.json (shared translations)
  └── Applies translations to data-i18n elements
```

## HTML Markup

Add `data-i18n="key"` to static text elements:

```html
<h1 data-i18n="page.title">My Application</h1>
<th data-i18n="table.email">Email</th>
<button data-i18n="button.save">Save</button>
<input data-i18n-placeholder="placeholder.search" placeholder="Search...">
```

## Script Loading

Add `DedgeAuth-i18n.js` after `user.js` in all HTML pages:

```html
<script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/user.js"></script>
<script src="api/DedgeAuth/ui/i18n.js"></script>
```

## JavaScript API

```javascript
DedgeAuth.t('table.email', 'Email');          // with fallback
DedgeAuth.t('message.itemCount', { count: 42 }); // with parameter
```

## Translation Files

Location: `wwwroot/i18n/nb.json` and `wwwroot/i18n/en.json`

Key naming convention:
- `nav.*` — Navigation items
- `page.*` — Page titles/subtitles
- `table.*` — Table headers
- `button.*` — Button labels
- `label.*` — Form labels
- `placeholder.*` — Input placeholders
- `message.*` — User messages
- `dialog.*` — Modal/dialog text

Both files must have the **exact same set of keys**.

## No Program.cs Changes Needed

`MapDedgeAuthProxy()` automatically registers `/api/i18n/languages` and `/api/i18n/{lang}` endpoints that serve files from `wwwroot/i18n/`.
